[h2]In-depth[/h2] 
[h3]‚öîÔ∏è Gameplay & Exploration: [/h3]  

Gang Beasts is a fighting game, where you either fight in teams or against each other. You have different types of game types. Arena, is the most common one, football and waves.

These are all fun to experience in groups of people and punch, kick, and head-bump in the most hilarious ways possible. This game will make you forget you're in a serious fight in seconds and just allow you to mash buttons, laugh out loud and just overall have a great time.

You have a large pool of areas to pick and choose and game modes to spice up the game however you and your friends want.

This game's quirky physics is what makes this game a total delight to play.

https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3183522191

[h3]üòÑ Fun: [/h3]

One of the best games to have fun in with. Whether you spend a few minutes or hours, this game will make sure you're having a blast all the time.

[h3]üèû Visuals & Presentation: [/h3]  

Its graphics make it easy to distinguish characters, and places of interests, dangerous areas to avoid. It's cute characters are a delight to look at even under the most brutal circumstances where one gets knocked out or thrown in front of a train.

https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3183521990

[h3]üîä Sound & Voice-Acting: [/h3]  

Though it may not seem extraordinary at first glance, the careless button mashing, punches, and kicks you land on characters infuse the gameplay with an irresistible blend of flair and punch, resulting in uproarious moments that are bound to leave you in stitches.

[h3]üìñ Story & Writing: [/h3]  

None existent. This game focuses on gameplay.

https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3183522529

[h3]üßµ Length & Difficulty: [/h3]  

As lengthy or as short as you want it to be. It's a game you play today, forget about it, play a few months or years later and it's just as fun.

Not a difficult game at all, but with the right skill you can pretty much dominate the ring if you understand what you're doing.

[h3]‚≠ïÔ∏èVerdict: [/h3]  
Gang Beasts stands out as the ideal game for enjoying with friends and family. Its dynamic combat mechanics spawn uproarious moments that are difficult to replicate. While it may offer brief gameplay sessions, the laughter and enjoyment it delivers will be some of the most memorable experiences you'll ever have.

review: Absolutely sucks. The opposite of intuitive controls. Even when I looked for the controls (hard to find them) and then learned them, they don't make any sense. Hit jump, you MIGHT jump, tap keys to move, you might move, grab? it's punch and hold i think? lift? is just lift your arms... there is no explanation for anything, no practice arena or way to learn. The UI / menus are absolutely not intuitive. I reset my input mappings like 3 times just trying to escape the menu with changes. Like, it feels like a 5th grader somehow made it, or was the development lead or wrote the requirements. TERRIBLE. feels like a free to play game that got cranked out in like 2 days for profit. Can't believe I spent money on this. I'd ask for it back if I could. AMAZED that the reviews are VERY POSITIVE. don't be fooled. it's insanely difficult to play. maybe that's what people like, but it should literally be called "Unplayable Game" so you know in advance you can't even count on the controls doing what they say they will. the videos make it look so easy but ti's not. nothing does what you expect. terrible. absolutely terrible.
